The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Nov. 7 (PTI): Delhi Universitys Ramjas College today decided to take action against its vice-principal and recommended his compulsory retirement after a panel indicted him for sexually harassing six male students.          
	The college complaint committee said the charges against B.N. Ray, who is also a senior faculty member in the political science department of the college, were valid.          
	The decision to force Ray into retirement was taken at an emergency meeting of the colleges governing body, after a section of students and teachers intensified protests against him in recent weeks. College officials said Ray hadnt been teaching since the allegations came to light and he was suspended in October 2007.                  
	 Chennai (PTI): A 40-year-old Korean, who headed a software firm in Chennai, allegedly committed suicide at his home on Thursday. Ryu Byeong Sang was found hanging from the ceiling by his wife when she returned home from a prayer meeting. The body has been flown to Korea after a post-mortem. Police said Sang could have committed suicide because of stress.                   
	 Malappuram (PTI): An Air India Airbus A310 from Jeddah tilted and its right wing grazed the runway while landing at Karippur International Airport in Malappuram on Friday. The incident occurred around 9.15am. There were 161 passengers onboard. No one was hurt.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): Lok Sabha Speaker Somnath Chatterjee, who had been admitted to the Army Research and Referral Hospital with pneumonia on Wednesday, is improving and is likely to be discharged soon.                   
	 Sonepat (PTI): The special ticket checking staff of Northern Railway hauled up 92 ticketless passengers at Sonepat on Friday. Some passengers were hiding in toilets and were brought out by Government Railway Police and Railway Protection Force personnel. Eleven passengers who failed to pay the fine have been jailed.
                                                                                                                         
